Inflation vs. Consumer Price Index (CPI), How They Are Different. The difference between the Consumer Price Index (CPI) and inflation is a source of confusion for many. At its easiest level, the Consumer Price Index in the United States is used to calculate inflation. Thus, their similarities are better understood based on that relationship even if the details of their differences are not.
